1377":"about 1377","1333":"1333","1377":"1377","Aft 1383":"after 1383","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Aston Bruley, Worcestershire, England":"Aston Magna, Worcestershire, England","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bruley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of French <b>Brûlé</b> (see   Brule  ). This surname is also found in Britain, where it is of Huguenot origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Brule","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Fernand, Lucien, Andre, Laurent, Marcel, Monique, Normand, Phillippe, Pierre, Raoul, Yvan, Yves.","French (<b>Brûlé</b>):","topographic name for someone living in a place cleared for use by burning, from <i>brûlé</i> ‘burnt’ (Old French <i>bruslé</i>, past participle of <i>brusler</i> ‘to burn’). Some instances of the name may derive from the same word used with reference to disfigurement by burning, either accidentally or as a medieval ordeal or punishment."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Bruley was born in 1360, in Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Henry Bruley and Unknown. She married William Bruley in 1374, in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died after 1383, in her hometown."},"et":{"1360–Aft 1383":"1360–pärast 1383","1360–1383":"1360–1383","1348–1436":"1348–1436","1377–Female":"1377–Surnud","1379–1446":"1379–1446","1383–1423":"1383–1423","1333–1360":"1333–1360","–Female":"Surnud","1374":"1374","Abt 1379":"umbes 1379","1383":"1383","1360":"1360","Abt 1383":"umbes 1383","1436":"1436","1348":"1348","1446":"1446","1423":"1423","1379":"1379","Abt 1377":"umbes 1377","1333":"1333","1377":"1377","Aft 1383":"pärast 1383","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Aston Bruley, Worcestershire, England":"Aston Magna, Worcestershire, England","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1360–Aft 1383":"1360–1383 jälkeen","1360–1383":"1360–1383","1348–1436":"1348–1436","1377–Female":"1377–Kuollut","1379–1446":"1379–1446","1383–1423":"1383–1423","1333–1360":"1333–1360","–Female":"Kuollut","1374":"1374","Abt 1379":"noin 1379","1383":"1383","1360":"1360","Abt 1383":"noin 1383","1436":"1436","1348":"1348","1446":"1446","1423":"1423","1379":"1379","Abt 1377":"noin 1377","1333":"1333","1377":"1377","Aft 1383":"1383 jälkeen","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Aston Bruley, Worcestershire, England":"Aston Magna, Worcestershire, England","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England